latestPosts.caption:
I’m in awe of Rajasthani architecture—there’s a story in every carving and a royal feeling in every stone. 
Mehrangarh Fort in Jodhpur is one of India’s most stunning and must-visit forts. Towering above the Blue City, it’s a perfect blend of history, grandeur, and intricate artistry. 
Built in the 15th century, it still stands tall with pride, echoing the legacy of the Rajputs.

If you’re ever in Rajasthan, don’t miss this masterpiece!
